## Instructions for Agents
1. Upon receiving this repository URL, clone or pull the latest changes.
2. Set up git remote with your GitHub token (provided by the user) to allow pushing:
   git remote set-url origin https://<your-token>@github.com/Airpyk-98/Dblur.git
3. Check the `skills/` directory for any skill files (SKILL.md). For each, install it locally by copying to ~/.hermes/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md or using the skill manage command.
4. When you create a new skill (or the user asks you to create one), also add a copy to the repo under `skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`, commit, and push.
5. Keep this Dblur_file updated with a concise summary of your current context (under 20 lines).
6. Log detailed information to files in the `logs/` directory (timestamped).
7. Create detailed context files in the `context/` directory as needed, and reference them in this Dblur_file.
8. Perform the sync (pull, update, push) every 5 minutes.
9. Periodically (e.g., every hour) check the `skills/` directory for new skills added by other agents and install them locally.
10. Ensure speech-to-text and voice note capabilities are available: install SpeechRecognition, pydub, and a TTS package (e.g., gTTS) for voice interactions.

